        },
        "question-10": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long does it take to inflate?",
            "text": "<p>All of our paddle boards come with an inflation pump, on average the first time you pump the board it will take longer so you are looking at around 15-20 minutes. Purchase the <a href=\"https://wavesupboards.com/products/battery-pump-20-psi\" title=\"Battery Pump | Inflatable Paddleboard & Kayak | 20 PSI\">electric pump</a> for 5 minute inflation!</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-11": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Which SUP is right for me?",
            "text": "<p>Our iSUP collections here at Wave are split into 4 key categories, covering beginner boards, family friendly all-rounders, intermediate skill level boards and our Pro range of professional performance paddle boards. Use our Board Comparison tool to find the perfect board just for you. </p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-12": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I take my SUP on a flight?",
            "text": "<p>Yes! The paddle board can be packed in the backpack/carry case provided in the kit for travel. Please check flight carry on luggage dimensions to see if the bag qualifies as a carry on.<br/><br/></p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_tQGT7W": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does my SUP package come with?",
            "text": "<p>Paddle, pump, storage and carry backpack, coiled ankle leash, detachable fin and a repair kit.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_geVGeB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What PSI should I inflate to?",
            "text": "<p>Although our Classic, Cruiser, Tourer and Woody paddle boards can be inflated to 15 PSI maximum, we advise inflating the iSUP to 12 PSI to allow some room for air expansion. Pro paddle boards can be inflated to 20 PSI, we advise inflating the iSUP to 15PSI.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_epdYar": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I take my dog on my SUP?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, most of our boards can take weight up to 130kg/285 lbs. </p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_kpHzwM": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do I need to wax my board?",
            "text": "<p>No, unlike surfboards iSUPS have EVA non-slip deck that provides grip, comfort and stability. </p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
